-- Sony’s Venture May Be Working on Game-Smartphone, WSJ Says
-- B y   M a r i k o   Y a s u
-- 2010-11-22T00:13:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-22/sony-s-venture-may-be-working-on-game-smartphone-wsj-says.html
Sony Corp. ’s phone venture with
Ericsson AB signaled it is developing a smartphone with a slide-
out controller designed to play games, the Wall Street Journal
reported, citing an interview with the head of the venture.  Bert Nordberg , chief executive officer of Sony Ericsson
Mobile Communications AB, said he’s aware of speculation about a
new product that would take advantage of Sony’s experience in
developing its portable game device, the report said. Nordberg
said he wants to make “noise” at the Mobile World Congress in
Barcelona in February, the Journal reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
